# One trunk

This exists because an automated agent left `HEAD` on a feature branch, launchd's
KeepAlive booted that branch, and the standard `backup_model` tool silently
vanished from the running bot while every meter stayed green. The fix is
structural, not vigilance.

## There is one trunk, and it is `main`

- The bot runs `main`. Every launch path goes through `ops/launch.sh`, which does
  `git checkout main` before the editable reinstall + exec. The launchd plist,
  `make run`, and `deploy.sh`'s restart all call that one script.
- Do not run the production bot on a feature branch. The CRITICAL `deployed_trunk`
  preflight probe refuses ready if the process is not on `main`, the build tree is
  dirty, or the build changed since boot — and it compares against the trunk and a
  once-per-process boot hash, so nothing can self-launder the way the old
  `running_code` WARN + "Restart: make run" did.

## "Running == source" is a build hash, not a sentinel

`src/build_hash.py` is the one content hash of the build (src + prompts + specs +
models.yaml). It is how `deployed_trunk` detects drift and how the live-outcome
receipt is keyed. Never reintroduce a boot sentinel that a probe re-writes on
every run — that is the self-laundering bug.

## The gate is the only door to main

- Work on a branch. Never commit or push directly to `main`. Merging to `main`
  needs an explicit ask (and the merge itself is the one place feature work lands).
- `scripts/gate.sh` is the single door: globbed lints + the structural-absence
  ledger + the unit suite. CI, the `ops/hooks/pre-push` hook, and `make gate` all
  call it, so the gate definition has one home and cannot drift.
- Green on the gate is the STATIC half of done. The RUNTIME half is
  `scripts/live_meter.py`: a real request genuinely completing on the trunk build,
  receipted to the build hash.
